Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.46,0:20:03.51,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,支持对卡特轮先生的不利判决 一家都没有\N{\rYUANWEN}that will ever, ever, ever, find against Mr. Catron,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.55,0:20:05.97,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,这可是事实\N{\rYUANWEN}and that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.05,0:20:08.39,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,如果我拒绝你的提议呢\N{\rYUANWEN}And what if I refuse your offer?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.06,0:20:15.27,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,那你就死定了\N{\rYUANWEN}You'll be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.36,0:20:21.36,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,给你24小时考虑\N{\rYUANWEN}You have 24 hours to give me an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.09,0:20:41.17,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,女士\N{\rYUANWEN}Senorita.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.26,0:20:43.13,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,先生\N{\rYUANWEN}Senor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.22,0:20:46.09,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,-你一个人吗  -是\N{\rYUANWEN}You're alone? - Si.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.18,0:20:48.22,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我想让你来见见我父亲\N{\rYUANWEN}I want you to come meet my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.22,0:20:52.93,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,走吧\N{\rYUANWEN}Shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.20,0:21:10.99,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,欢迎\N{\rYUANWEN}Bienvenido.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.08,0:21:16.08,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,你紧张吗\N{\rYUANWEN}Are you nervous?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.17,0:21:17.50,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,不会有事的\N{\rYUANWEN}You'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.29,0:21:22.55,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,爸爸 这就是威廉·邦尼\N{\rYUANWEN}Papa, this is William Bonney.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.63,0:21:28.34,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,这就是大家口中的比利小子吧\N{\rYUANWEN}Otherwise known, I believe, as Billy the Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.64,0:21:34.14,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,很高兴认识你\N{\rYUANWEN}Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.23,0:21:38.10,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我的荣幸 先生\N{\rYUANWEN}It's my honor, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.19,0:21:39.94,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,请进吧\N{\rYUANWEN}Please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.51,0:22:11.14,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我是无论如何也想不到\N{\rYUANWEN}I could have never imagined that I would be here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.22,0:22:13.39,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,今天居然会和一个著名的法外之徒聊天\N{\rYUANWEN}talking to a famous outlaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.47,0:22:16.14,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,生活很奇怪 邦尼先生\N{\rYUANWEN}Life is strange, Mr. Bonney.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.41,0:22:36.50,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,不用了 谢谢先生\N{\rYUANWEN}No, gracias, senor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.58,0:22:40.33,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我女儿跟我说你已经公开宣布\N{\rYUANWEN}My daughter tells me that you've abjured
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.42,0:22:42.33,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,走入正途了\N{\rYUANWEN}the outlaw life?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.46,0:22:44.04,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,约翰·汤斯顿先生\N{\rYUANWEN}Mr. John Tunstall offered me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.17,0:22:46.96,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,给我提供了一个不错的工作 我接受了\N{\rYUANWEN}a good job working for him, and I took it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.09,0:22:50.63,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,约翰·汤斯顿那个英国人 嗯 我听过他的故事\N{\rYUANWEN}John Tunstall, the Englishman. Yes, I've heard of him- - stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.76,0:22:54.01,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,他好像跟墨菲少校发生了争执\N{\rYUANWEN}He seems to be in a quarrel with Major Murphy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.10,0:22:57.60,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,当然我本人是不喜欢参与这些事的\N{\rYUANWEN}Of course I don't involve myself in such matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.68,0:23:00.64,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,那你的信仰呢 邦尼先生\N{\rYUANWEN}- What about faith, Mr. Bonney? - Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.77,0:23:03.11,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,你有信仰吗\N{\rYUANWEN}Do you have it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.19,0:23:05.07,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,先生 这个世界我见得多了\N{\rYUANWEN}Sir, I've seen enough of this world to know
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.15,0:23:07.19,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,知道并没有什么上帝在天上眷顾着我\N{\rYUANWEN}that there's no one up there looking out for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.24,0:23:11.61,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我曾有过一个朋友\N{\rYUANWEN}I had a friend once.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.74,0:23:14.20,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,在他身上发生了特别糟糕的事\N{\rYUANWEN}Something really bad happened to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.24,0:23:16.62,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,他说 我失去了对上帝的信仰\N{\rYUANWEN}"He lost his faith in God, "he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.70,0:23:19.50,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,他再也不去做弥撒了\N{\rYUANWEN}He never went to mass again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.58,0:23:23.08,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,在他临终之时我去看他\N{\rYUANWEN}And when he was on his deathbed, I went to see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.17,0:23:25.42,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我握着他的手 问他\N{\rYUANWEN}I held his hand. And I asked him,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.46,0:23:28.21,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,你还是无神论者吗\N{\rYUANWEN}”Are you still an atheist? "
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.30,0:23:32.59,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,他看着我说道 是的 我还是无神论者\N{\rYUANWEN}He looks up at me and said, "Yes, still an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.68,0:23:34.22,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,感谢上帝\N{\rYUANWEN}Thank God. "
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.68,0:23:42.19,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,请进\N{\rYUANWEN}Please. Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.74,0:24:00.04,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,请坐\N{\rYUANWEN}Sit, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.25,0:24:07.50,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,你为什么对我女儿感兴趣呢 邦尼先生\N{\rYUANWEN}Why are you interested in my daughter, Mr. Bonney?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.59,0:24:12.42,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,-说实话吗 先生  -拜托\N{\rYUANWEN}- Truth be told, sir? - Por favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.09,0:24:15.51,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我爱她\N{\rYUANWEN}I love her.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.60,0:24:17.60,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,而且我 我想娶她\N{\rYUANWEN}And I- I wanna marry her.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.27,0:24:26.23,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我的上帝啊\N{\rYUANWEN}Ay, Dios mio.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.19,0:24:33.20,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,这些人都是我的祖先\N{\rYUANWEN}These are all my ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.53,0:24:37.32,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,他们是永远不可能答应的\N{\rYUANWEN}And they would never approve of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.83,0:24:46.54,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,先生 美国是个新生国家\N{\rYUANWEN}Sir, America is a new country.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.63,0:24:49.34,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,美国人也不太会\N{\rYUANWEN}And the Americans don't rightly hold on
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.42,0:24:52.09,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,坚持古老的传统\N{\rYUANWEN}to a lot of the old traditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.13,0:24:54.34,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,在某些事上 我赞同他们 但有一些我不赞同\N{\rYUANWEN}In some ways, I agree with them. In others, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.43,0:24:57.22,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,但如果要说一个女人是否有权\N{\rYUANWEN}But when it comes to whether a woman should choose
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.26,0:25:01.64,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,选择自己的丈夫 这点我跟美国人的看法是一致的\N{\rYUANWEN}who she wants to marry, I'm with the Americans.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.31,0:25:07.48,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我认为你女儿应该有自己的选择\N{\rYUANWEN}I think your daughter deserves that choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.79,0:25:30.34,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,欢迎回来 约翰\N{\rYUANWEN}- Welcome back, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.42,0:25:31.25,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,很高兴见到你\N{\rYUANWEN}Good to see you. -
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.34,0:25:33.26,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,你感觉如何\N{\rYUANWEN}How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.34,0:25:37.18,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,比之前好多了 麦格斯文太太\N{\rYUANWEN}Well, a lot better than I was feeling, Mrs. McSween.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.26,0:25:39.22,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我感觉是如此\N{\rYUANWEN}- I can tell you that much. -
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.30,0:25:40.43,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,需要帮助吗\N{\rYUANWEN}Want some help, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.47,0:25:42.56,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,不不不 我可以的\N{\rYUANWEN}Oh, no, no, no. I can manage.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.64,0:25:45.10,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,先请\N{\rYUANWEN}After you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.48,0:25:54.40,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,布雷迪警长和他的手下 包括比利\N{\rYUANWEN}Sheriff Brady and his posse, including Billy,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.49,0:25:56.70,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,逮捕了杰西·埃文斯和他团伙的五名成员\N{\rYUANWEN}arrested Jesse Evans and five members of his gang
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.78,0:26:00.45,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,并将他们关在镇上的地下监狱里\N{\rYUANWEN}and locked them up in the cellar jail in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.37,0:26:05.62,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,-他们还在里面吗  -嗯\N{\rYUANWEN}- They still there? - Mm- hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.79,0:26:10.71,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,但我们得到消息称 他们将因盗窃\N{\rYUANWEN}But we got news that they are arraigned to appear in court
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.75,0:26:14.42,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,以及试图谋杀一名正在执行任务的美国警长等罪\N{\rYUANWEN}on several counts of theft and the attempted murder
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.51,0:26:18.43,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,被传讯出庭\N{\rYUANWEN}of a United States Sheriff in the course of his duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.51,0:26:19.59,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,什么时候\N{\rYUANWEN}When?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.68,0:26:23.22,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,一周后\N{\rYUANWEN}About a week's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.93,0:26:29.19,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,法律还是决定出手对付浩世了\N{\rYUANWEN}The law has finally acted against the House.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.27,0:26:34.40,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我是说 我们应该庆祝一下\N{\rYUANWEN}I mean, we ought to celebrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.78,0:26:40.82,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我想我该回家了\N{\rYUANWEN}I think I ought to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.91,0:26:45.37,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我还是觉得有点累\N{\rYUANWEN}I still feel a little tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.41,0:26:49.29,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,当然\N{\rYUANWEN}Yes. Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.37,0:26:51.42,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,那你先回家好好休息一下吧\N{\rYUANWEN}Why don't you go home and, um, get some rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.50,0:26:52.88,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我明天过去看你\N{\rYUANWEN}I'lI come over tomorrow, if you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.96,0:26:54.46,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,好\N{\rYUANWEN}Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.34,0:27:00.43,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我没搞明白\N{\rYUANWEN}Yeah. I- - I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.51,0:27:02.39,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,你为什么不想让他们被审判呢\N{\rYUANWEN}Why don't you want this trial to take place?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.47,0:27:04.43,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我们一直努力奋斗不就为了这一天吗\N{\rYUANWEN}It's what we've all been fighting for.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.47,0:27:08.64,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我花了点时间仔细想了一下\N{\rYUANWEN}Well, I've had time to think things through,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.73,0:27:13.69,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我认为这场审判只会让事情变得更糟\N{\rYUANWEN}and I think this trial will only make things worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.77,0:27:17.36,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,但我有个计划\N{\rYUANWEN}But I have a plan- -
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.40,0:27:21.28,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,一个可以让这场战争\N{\rYUANWEN}a plan that might actually put an end to this war,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.32,0:27:23.24,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,还没开始就会结束的计划\N{\rYUANWEN}even before it's really started.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.32,0:27:25.83,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,这包括帮助杰西和他的手下逃狱\N{\rYUANWEN}It involves helping Jesse and his gang escape from jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.91,0:27:27.87,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,什么 我们为什么要这么做啊\N{\rYUANWEN}What? Why would we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.95,0:27:29.62,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,听我说 比利\N{\rYUANWEN}Hear me out, Billy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.71,0:27:31.87,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,如果我们把杰西和他手下从监狱里救出来\N{\rYUANWEN}If we can spring Jesse and the others from jail,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.00,0:27:35.92,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,那我们和浩世之间就可以\N{\rYUANWEN}then I believe it could lead to some sort of accommodation
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.96,0:27:38.55,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,达成某种和解 我们 我们可以结束斗争\N{\rYUANWEN}between us and the House. We - We could end the fighting
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.63,0:27:41.34,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,然后共享林肯县大把\N{\rYUANWEN}and share the many economic opportunities
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.43,0:27:45.43,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,既有的经济机会\N{\rYUANWEN}that I know exist right here in Lincoln County.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.51,0:27:47.64,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,你确定墨菲愿意和解吗\N{\rYUANWEN}And you're sure Murphy's ready to make peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.68,0:27:49.60,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,他知道浩世陷入了很大困难\N{\rYUANWEN}He knows the House is in a lot of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.68,0:27:53.40,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,他需要新的合作伙伴和新投资\N{\rYUANWEN}He needs new partners, new investment.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.48,0:27:58.48,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我真心认为 若我们肯伸出橄榄枝\N{\rYUANWEN}I truly believe that this... gesture of goodwill
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.57,0:28:00.57,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,应该可以改变一切\N{\rYUANWEN}could change everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.65,0:28:06.91,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,汤森顿先生 我真希望能跟你一样乐观\N{\rYUANWEN}And I truly wish I could share in your optimism, Mr. Tunstall.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.45,0:28:10.45,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,但我了解杰西·埃文斯\N{\rYUANWEN}But I know Jesse Evans,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.58,0:28:13.92,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,你伸出的橄榄枝对他来说毫无意义\N{\rYUANWEN}and gestures of goodwill mean nothing to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.00,0:28:16.42,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我不赞成这个计划\N{\rYUANWEN}I do not support this plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.50,0:28:20.30,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,比利 我给了你人生的第二次机会\N{\rYUANWEN}I have given you a second chance in life, Billy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.38,0:28:22.88,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我希望你用忠心来回报\N{\rYUANWEN}In return, I expect your loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.86,0:28:38.57,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,爸爸 我能跟你坐下聊会吗\N{\rYUANWEN}Papa, may I join you?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.65,0:28:42.57,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,来啊 坐\N{\rYUANWEN}Please. Sit.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.58,0:28:50.66,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,你想什么呢\N{\rYUANWEN}What were you thinking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.75,0:28:53.46,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,想你母亲呢\N{\rYUANWEN}About your mother
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.54,0:28:55.37,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,想我们结婚多久了\N{\rYUANWEN}and how long we have been married
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.50,0:28:58.25,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,还有我是如何将她的付出当做理所当然的\N{\rYUANWEN}and how much I've taken her for granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.47,0:29:09.43,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,你喜欢比利吗\N{\rYUANWEN}Did you like Billy?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.59,0:29:43.96,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,他想娶你\N{\rYUANWEN}He wants to marry you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.09,0:29:47.55,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,-他 他自己说的吗  -嗯\N{\rYUANWEN}- Did...did he say that? - Mm- hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.64,0:29:50.68,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,而且我觉得他是认真的\N{\rYUANWEN}And I think he means it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.72,0:29:53.35,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,那你怎么说的\N{\rYUANWEN}And what did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.66,0:30:16.58,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,我给他讲了我们的祖先们\N{\rYUANWEN}I told him about our ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.66,0:30:18.67,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,可以说他让我\N{\rYUANWEN}And let's say that he made me
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.75,0:30:19.96,YIWEN,,0,0,0,,以全新的角度\N{\rYUANWEN}- see them in a.
